<h2>What this partner does</h2>
<p>Describe a system you're trying to diagram — Earth's four subsystems, the carbon cycle, the ice-albedo loop — and the Diagrammer asks you what the components are, where the arrows should go, and which interactions are feedback loops. It will catch causal direction errors and ask you to justify each arrow.</p>

<h2>What this partner won't do</h2>
<p>It won't draw the diagram for you, and it won't give you the "right" diagram. Systems diagrams are arguments — there are better and worse versions, but not single correct ones. The Diagrammer helps you build a defensible version of yours.</p>

